### Provider API Tests
### Tests for ProviderController endpoints
### Self-contained: no dynamic IDs needed.
### Run requests top-to-bottom.

### List all available providers
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/providers
Content-Type: application/json

> {%
  client.assert(response.status === 200 || response.status === 500, "List providers should return 200 or 500");
  client.log("Providers response: " + response.status);
%}

### Get specific provider by name
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/providers/zai
Content-Type: application/json

> {%
  client.assert(response.status === 200 || response.status === 500, "Get provider should return 200 or 500");
  client.log("Provider response: " + response.status);
%}

### Start OAuth authorization for provider
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/providers/zai/oauth/authorize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "redirect_uri": "http://localhost:8080/callback"
}

> {%
  client.assert(response.status === 200, "OAuth authorize should return 200");
  client.log("OAuth authorization started");
%}

### Handle OAuth callback for provider (GET — controller uses @GetMapping)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/providers/zai/oauth/callback?code=auth_code&state=state123
Content-Type: application/json

> {%
  client.log("OAuth callback response: " + response.status);
%}
